  <description><![CDATA[<p><strong>Summer Holidays in Madeira - Madeira </strong></p>
<p><strong>Lakes and Mountains - Summer Holidays in Baveno - Lake Maggiore, Piedmont</strong></p>
<ul class="unIndentedList">
<li>Funchal sea level - Pico do Arieiro 1,818m above sea level</li>
</ul>
<p>Summer holidays in Madeira whisk you away to a wonderful island, set in the Atlantic Ocean some 600 miles south west of mainland Europe. The Portuguese island of Madeira is blessed with a mild climate, making summer holidays in Madeira enduringly popular with British tourists.</p>
<p>The capital of the island is Funchal. You'll enjoy visiting Funchal on your summer holiday in Madeira, a bustling city that tumbles down the hillside to the harbour and yacht marina. The city stands in a gorgeous natural amphitheatre surrounded by green mountains, soaring peaks and stunning coastal scenery. So a summer holiday in Madeira is ideal if you want to leave everyday life far, far behind.</p>
<p>Take summer holidays in Madeira and you'll love the island's high standard hotels. The people are very are friendly and service is always courteous. Stunning valleys, the Laurissilva forest, wonderful gardens and flowers make this a paradise on earth. Walk the levadas, a network of dramatic irrigation channels, play golf, fish or just relax by the pool in beautiful surroundings.</p>]]></description>
