<p>Set in the Atlantic Ocean some 600 miles southwest of mainland Europe, the Portugese island of Madeira is blessed with a mild climate. The capital of the island is Funchal, a bustling city that tumbles down the hillside to the harbour and yacht marina. The city, stands in a natural amphitheatre surrounded by green mountains, soaring peaks and stunning coastal scenery. Madeira is an ideal holiday destination for those wanting to leave the stress of everyday life behind. The hotel standards are high, the people are friendly and the service is courteous. Stunning valleys, the Laurissilva forest, wonderful gardens and flowers make it a paradise on earth. Walk the “levadas”, the network of irrigation channels, play golf, fish or just relax by the pool in beautiful surroundings.</p>]]></listingDescription>
