  <walkingDescription><![CDATA[<p>The island offers over 500 miles of "Levada" walks following the original irrigation channels built to carry water down the mountains. These are graded from simple strolls to more challenging hikes and are one of the best ways to appreciate Madeira's spectacular scenery and diverse topography. Visitors can simply buya map and access walks by using Madeira's excellent local bus system or join a tour with an experienced guide. The minibus drive to the start and end of these guided walks are usually a scenic excursion in their own right. Stout walking boots are recommended.</p>
